    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hello,</p>

<p>I'm trying to use Zend_Date with an array to get the result 2010-02-01 00:00
I also checked in the documentation, what is not specified is equal to 0.</p>

<p>So lets try :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$endDate    = new Zend_Date(array(
    'year'   =&gt; 2010,
    'month'  =&gt; 2,
    'day'    =&gt; 1
));

Zend_Debug::dump($endDate-&gt;toString('yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm'));
</code></pre>

<p>The system return :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
string(16) "2010-02-01 00:30"
</code></pre>

<p>There is 30 minutes here for nothing, I can refresh this minutes stay.</p>

<p>My current timezone is Asia/Singapore and I am in DST.</p>

<p>I tryed to take a look.
I found, when I put mktime = false for the function mktime, the system use mktime instead of gmmktime and everything is ok</p>

<p>I hope it will be helpfull</p>

<p>Best Regards</p>

